                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>1 papyrus ; 35.4 x 29 cm.</support>
                        <condition>
                           <ab type="conservation">This sheet of papyrus has a dark brown color; it is regularly cut at the top and bottom; it seems that this document has been written in two columns; only few letters at the end of the first column are survived; fibers are frayed and removed at the right side. There are two kolleses at the middle and at the very right side of the sheet. In addition to, at least 6 vertical folds, the papyrus was also diagonally folded; some holes and lacunae are being result of these folds. At least a vertical portion of ca. 8 cm has been lost at the left hand side, which can be notice from the upper part where it is extended that distance to the right; and of ca. 4 cm. in length. The surface is damaged at several parts.</ab>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <ab type="lines">16</ab>
                           <ab type="recto-verso">Source of description: Recto</ab>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <p>Written along the fibers in medium-sized semi cursive letters; well practiced business hand; the scribe used a thick nib. The intercolumniation between the tow columns is 2.0 cm; the interlinear spaces are even of 0.5 cm. The document has many abbreviations, signs, diereses, colon and stichometric letters with a horizontal stroke over the numbers. The letters are characterized by short form. Since the average of lines in the column is 32 and the last numbered line is 99; so, the document is consists of, at least, 3 columns.</p>
                  </handDesc>
